I think pickpocketing is different than lockpicking and poison making. Locked doors are static and poisons can be made at any time. But, to steal from an npc it must be up and have the item in posession, then there's the chance you're caught. It's a more dynamic thing than opening a door. I don't know but I *doubt* a true ALL/ALL quest would require one specific classes abilities in a dynamic sense like that, but I might be mistaken. Time will tell. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufaulk60.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faulk60</A> at: 1/5/02 11:10:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urassyfleetfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rassy Fleetfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/6/02 1:14:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3680.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sanctus Seru Earring of Veracity-Bregun Dorey quest</span><hr size=1> did you just stumble on this quest by saying i will gather information? i couldnt get him to say anything to me after speaking to him earlier. <br>
